ider the debate on industrialization in india which is relevant for other lateindustrializers the fourth part is on liberalization with a focus on india it evaluates the indian experience with stabilization adjustment and reform which is then situated in its wider political and historical context show more liberalization and development deepak nayyar table of contents preface to the paperback edition preface introduction i theory  macroeconomics in developing countries  macroeconomics of structural adjustment and public finances in developing countries  on exclusion and inclusion democracy markets and people ii development  development through globalization  learning to unlearn from development  shorttermism public policies and economic development  work livelihood and rights iii industrialization  international relocation of production and industrialization in less developed countries  themes in trade and industrialization  industrial development in india growth or stagnation  the foreign trade sector planning and industrialization in india iv liberalization  macroeconomic reforms in india shortterm effects and longrun implications  economic reforms in india understanding the process and learning from experience  economic development and political democracy interaction of economics and politics in independent india  indias unfinished journey transforming growth into development acknowledgements index liberalization and development deepak nayyar author information deepak nayyar is professor of economics jawaharlal nehru university new delhi share also of interest catch up deepak nayyar reshaping tomorrow ejaz ghani two nations indivisible shannon k oneil catch up deepak nayyar indias economy performance and challenges shankar acharya and rakesh mohan securing the world economy patricia p clavin trade and globalization oip deepak nayyar facilitating trade and global competitiveness arpita mukherjee parthapratim pal subrata mitra indias reforms jagdish bhagwati and ar